thread.title: Seattle Times’ High School football rankings, Oct. 8
thread.title_full: Seattle Times’ High School football rankings, Oct. 8 | The Seattle Times

author: Solange Reyner
title: Seattle Times’ High School football rankings, Oct. 8
text:
Class 4A Top 10 
1. Lake Stevens (5-0) 
Beat Cascade, 48-0. Next: Friday at Monroe, 7 p.m.
2. Camas (5-0) 
Beat Skyview, 42-10. Next: Friday vs. Battle Ground, 7 p.m.
3. Gig Harbor (5-0) 
Beat South Kitsap, 65-0. Next: Thursday at Timberline, 7 p.m.
4. Gonzaga Prep (5-0) 
Beat Shadle Park, 48-14. Next: Friday vs. University, 7 p.m.
5. Graham-Kapowsin (5-0) 
Beat Spanaway Lake, 35-0. Next: Thurs. vs. Skyline, 7 p.m.
6. Skyline (5-0) 
Beat Redmond, 46- 14. Next: Thursday at Graham-Kapowsin, 7 p.m.
7. Olympia (5-0) 
Beat Issaquah, 32-14. Next: Friday at Stadium, 7 p.m.
8. Bellarmine Prep (4-1) 
Beat Timberline, 35-6. Next: Friday at South Kitsap, 7 p.m.
9. Richland (4-1) 
Beat Walla Walla, 31-19. Next: Friday at Kennewick, 7 p.m.
10. University (5-0) 
Beat Rogers, 50-7. Next: Friday at Gonzaga Prep, 7 p.m.
Class 3A Top 10 
1. Eastside Catholic (5-0) 
Beat Seattle Prep, 54-10. Next: Friday vs. Bishop Blanchet, 7 p.m.
2. Bellevue (3-1) 
Beat Glacier Peak, 24-6. Next: Friday at Juanita, 7 p.m.
3. Lincoln (5-0) 
Beat Mount Tahoma, 67-14. Next: Friday at North Thurston, 7 p.m.
4. Bishop Blanchet (5-0) 
Beat O’Dea, 34-21. Next: Friday at Eastside Catholic, 7 p.m.
5. Glacier Peak (4-1) 
Lost to Bellevue, 24-6. Next: Fri. vs. Mountlake Terrace, 7 p.m.
6. Lakes (5-0) 
Beat Bonney Lake, 27-7. Next: Friday vs. Auburn Mountainview, 7 p.m.
7. O’Dea (4-1) 
Lost to Bishop Blanchet, 33-21. Next: Friday vs. Bainbridge, 7 p.m.
8. Sumner (5-0) 
Beat Peninsula, 21-20. Next: Friday vs. Auburn, 7 p.m.
9. Peninsula (2-3) 
Lost to Sumner, 21-20. Next: Friday at Enumclaw, 7 p.m.
10. Auburn Mountainview (3-1) 
Beat Auburn Riverside, 36-17. Next: Friday at Lakes, 7 p.m.
